snippet.textDisplay:
@Channel Awesome I have STILL NOT SEEN The Rise of Skywalker yet... But The Force Awakens was GREAT in my personal view, set up great ideas... Then The Last Jedi came along and... Well, You hit the nail on the head!!! Rian Johnson is a Great Director - But HE DOES NOT DO SEQUELS! And BOY IT SHOWS... Every plot thread he created he also CLOSED!!! So yeah... Where was JJ Abrams going to go...???

I have so many ideas myself that COULD HAVE WORKED... I actually LOVED the idea that Rey was NOT Important... NOT a Bloodline, So to throw it away... WOW! THAT'S BAD!

But frankly, Yeah... Disney did a Lucas but WAY WORSE! I know us fans defend Lucas to our deaths - But reality is... He made BILLIONS from Merchandise, and with that he also sacrificed his vision - The Visual Encyclopedias that were released Pre-Internet say that Luke, Han and Leia are HUMAN... Now repeated on Wookiepedia, but in 1980 in a PRINT INTERVIEW... Back when people read Newspapers Lucas said "There are no Humans in my movies, Its a Galaxy Far, Far Away... Everyone is an Alien" - But Money speaks and the BOOKS ARE MERCHANDISE... So he canonised that they are Human, Which in turn SCREWED UP the Timeline as now every fan sees the franchise as running in REAL TIME as we know it... While they were Alien we could use our imaginations and say "Oh maybe they live longer etc..."

Yes, Sorry Fans - And believe me, I am one of you having first seen Star Wars when I was 5 back in 1978... Lucas did put money before Story... BUT DISNEY!!! OH THEY LITERALLY LOOKED AT THIS AS A BUSINESS VENTURE! At least Lucas WANTED TO TELL A GOOD STORY!

Disney well and truly screwed up... They started out so well too... If only they had listened and gave JJ Abrams what he wanted - There are interviews people can watch online where he and Kathleen Kennedy BOTH WANTED MORE TIME to work on The Force Awakens, But were told NO - A NEW TRILOGY MOVIE EVERY TWO YEARS! Is it any wonder why JJ didn't actually want to come back?

Seriously, What the fuck has happened to Disney? When you look at it as I am now... You realise that even their GOOD Live Action Remakes of their classic Movies are simply there as a BUSINESS VENTURE... Not to update a classic, not to introduce a new fan base to classic tales, it is all about the QUICK CASH GRAB... MONEY NOW CREATIVITY LATER!

God it hurts me more as I do see so many good ideas with these movies being WASTED for the sheer hell of corporate greed - YES... EVEN THE LAST JEDI! THERE IS A GOOD MOVIE THERE SOMEWHERE BUT ITS BURIED UNDER CORPORATE GREED!

Kylo believed that his mother wouldn't accept him anymore and that he could never return. In the end, Leia uses all of her strength to reach him and essentially tell Kylo she still loves him despite what happened.

So here's what should have happened. After that scene where Hux let everyone go, he should have taken over the First Order at that point (instead of getting shot by Pryde, he takes over from Pryde). Then let's jump to Rylo...
The Leia distracting him thing could be seen as Rylo as Leia trying to weaken him (since it leads to Rey stabbing him). Rylo, renouncing his family once and for all, goes back to Palpatine to sneak around and essentially once he finds out Rey killing him would mean she'd get his power/soul, stabs Palpatine in the back during the ritual, essentially drawing all of his power/soul into him...
Final battle is Rey vs Rylo. Rylo quickly knocking away Luke's lightsaber only to find, Rey also has Leia's!
Meanwhile, as the battle rages in the air between the Rebels and the Final Order (Grey Ships), suddenly the First Order (White Ships) shows up and does battle with the Final Order. Then to tie in the "Holdo Maneuver", Hux in a fit of rage and wanting to kill Kylo somehow sets it up that all of the White Ships jump to light speed at once, not only shredding much of the Grey Ships but essentially destroy the already unstable planet so it will explode any moment.
Back to Rey vs Rylo, she and him both absorb the powers of their respective sides of the force and are dead even in a force struggle. But then who shows up for the lost lightsaber but Finn, who made it to the ground to help her. Finn is good enough with the lightsaber to provide enough distraction to Rylo to have Rey defeat him in a huge explosion of force energy.
Rey is dead, but just to try to mimic what he saw Rey do earlier with the worm, Finn tries to heal her and succeeds. It turns out since he was close enough to the blast he actually absorbed a little bit of force energy that he was able to pass back into Rey while telling her how he feels about her. She revives and after kissing Finn (or not) he passes out...The planet explodes...

3. Gives Finn better purpose and ties up his story much better.
4. By having Finn assisting Rey, it showing that the importance of support by the non-powered individuals and that by making the choice to be good or bad, they are the true tide turners in the war.
